up, thinking he might want to share in some of the fun.  He accepted my invite, but then informed of his guilds following policies:<br>
<br>
BTW, this isn't mean to trash them or anything, just let you know what happened and what their policies are.<br>
<br>
(1)  He couldn't help me fight against a human ranger.  This was because the ranger "worhsipped Tunare" and therefore wasn't allowed to be killed.<br>
<br>
(2)  He couldn't help me fight against a dwarf rogue and a halfling druid.  This is because they were shorties, and their guild doesn't attack "pure" shorties.  (Not sure what he meant by pure... I was in the middle of dying when he made the comment)<br>
<br>
(3)  He also wouldn't help out with any other foreigner in Greater Faydark if that person was accompanied by another elf.  That is their "escort" rule.<br>
<br>
<br>
Heh, I wasn't too happy as he watched me die...  Anyways, nothing bad against Dal Kingdom.  If that's how they wish to play their guild, that's their perrogative.<br>
<br>
I'm just glad we have an elf guild with some backbone now... ;)<br>
<br>
- Tul <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub45.ezboard.com/udorkmid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dorkmid</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#660000>(2/15/01 11:44:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dal Kingdom Update</span><hr size=1> Here-here!<br>
<br>
We are all going to be bruised, cut, battered and burned before the rest of the server begins to respect us.  Some will never follow our ways - which is OK because conflict is the essense of the world - in all its forms IMHO.<br>
<br>
The response we have gotten, and the comments that have been made only serve to strengthen my resolve that we are doing the right thing for the server as a whole.  Misplaced accusations of 'grief play', and 'rules violations' warm my heart.  After elves and others in Kelethin have been handed thier bum on a plate by a GM, then maybe they will start to respect us.<br>
<br>
People are afraid to stretch the edge of their comfort zones; but, that is the only way to grow.<br>
<br>
My 2cp. <p>Dorkmid 
