<br>
My sister, Alanie, is in Dal Kingdom, and she tells me that only those guilds they have treaties with are exempt from attack. The escort business is about a DAL KINGDOM elf escorting a non-elf OFF our lands and does not apply to any other circumstance. At no time is a Dal Kingdom elf allowed to group with any non-elf, despite any treaties they might have with mixed race guilds.<br>
<br>
What gods others worship is of no concern. A Dal Kingdom member is obligated to assist all elves, though there are certain exceptions (if the elf is breaking rules, like not scooting, or is bindrushing, for instance).<br>
<br>
I know you don't want to be a trouble maker or sound like a complainer, but this charter is very new to Dal Kingdom and the adjustments are difficult to monitor. It's really important that the leadership knows before it gets to be a bad habit too hard to break. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub45.ezboard.com/utearis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tearis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#660000>(2/15/01 2:04:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dal Kingdom Update</span><hr size=1> Greetings,<br>
<br>
I've spoken with the koada'vie you were with.  He has been gone for six months and was still uncertain about certain rules of engagement.  <br>
<br>
The policy adopted by the noble houses ruling the Dal Kingdom is<br>
<br>
1) Any who cross elven lands are to be asked to leave in peace or be removed with force.  They may request permission to cross elven lands (or their guild may).  Elven lands are considered to be Firiona Vie, Greater and Lesser Faydark.<br>
<br>
2.  Outside elven lands (i.e. Mistmoore), it is discretionary with respect to other followers of good deities as to treatment.  Elves are the only race which has no evil gods.  As good folk, acts of kindness toward other servants of good are encouraged but not required.  Servants of evil and evil races are to be slain anywhere at anytime.<br>
<br>
This is reflected in our charter and subject to editing by voting members of the court.  Illuvitae is extended an offer to become a voting member of the Court to help shape a policy which will fit with preserving our race.<br>
<br>
Walk with the Mother,<br>
<br>
Tearis Thex<br>
King of the Dal<br>
